==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[trimillennialis]]'' from ''[[tri]]'' + ''mill-'' thousand + ''[[ennius|enni(us)]]'' year- -al

===Noun===
'''trimillennial'''
# The 3,000th [[anniversary]] of an event or happening.

===Adjective===
'''trimillennial'''
# Occuring every thousand (2,000) [[year]]s and 2 [[millennium|millennia]].

====Translations====
*Italian: [[trimillenniale]]
*Latin: [[trimillennialis]]